inn1.comm: Kyle Mills starts things off for New Zealand, first ball is on target, back of a length, on off, Marsh defends
pitches it further up this time, in the channel outside off, Marsh pokes it towards point
ooh, beaten as he tries to defend that one, pitched on a length on off and just moved away a touch
a bit wider outside off, Marsh takes a couple of steps down the track but decided to shoulder arms
similar ball, this time Marsh walks out of his crease and defends towards mid-off
first runs for Marsh and Australia, overpitched outside off and he cracks that through the gap between mid-off and extra cover
back of a length, on middle and off, Warner pulls that, New Zealand have a man at the midwicket boundary who does the fielding
big shout for lbw, angling across the batsman, pitched on the leg stump, and came back in a touch, umpire rules it not out, gives the benefit of doubt to the batsman
on the middle and leg, Marsh shuffles across and flicks it away to deep mid wicket
flicked towards short midwicket, straight to the fielder, there's no time to pick up a single
on the middle and leg, Marsh tucks it to mid wicket
punched back to the bowler, who does well to field it during his follow-through
back of a length, just outside off, Warner cuts it toward point
similar length, slightly wider outside off, Warner lets it go, the ball bounces once more before it reaches the keeper
short ball, on legstump, Warner tries to tuck it towards the legstump, but doesn't connect with the ball
short of a length, not too much space to cut, Warner goes for the stroke anyway, gets beaten as the bounce is higher than he expected
a bit more room for Warner to work with this time, he chops the ball towards backward point
pitched up, just outside off, Marsh gets on the front foot and pushes it towards mid-off, calls early for the single
a hint of swing for Southee as he maintains a full length, Marsh shows the full face of the bat as he defends it back to the bowler
slightly shorter and about a foot outside off, Marsh jabs it towards Jeetan Patel at backward point
tries to defend it on the backfoot, gets a thick edge and the ball drops at his feet
full and on middle and leg, Marsh turns it away towards midwicket, straight to the fielder
Shot! wonderfully timed punch past the bowler for four, that was played on the up
keeps the length full, pitches just outside off, blocked back to the bowler
short outside the offstump, cut to cover point
back of a length and outside off again, nudged towards cover, a misfield allows the batsmen time to pinch a single
closer to the stumps, Marsh opens the face of the bat to run it towards backward point
outside off, Marsh shoulders arms to that one
short of a length ball, in the channel outside off, Marsh wanted to guide it to third man, beaten by the extra bounce
a similar delivery, Marsh leaves this one alone
good ball to start the over, length and on off, Warner is squared up as he defends off the backfoot
full delivery on off, Warner crunches it to mid-off, whose on the edge of the circle, giving the batsmen time to take a single
looking to cut but gets a bottom edge to the keeper
overpitched on legstump, flicked away towards Grant Elliott at midwicket
better line and length, a touch short and on offstump, solid defence from Marsh
on the pads, Marsh doesn't manage to place his leg-glance very well, straight to the man atshort fine leg
Warner dabs a short ball to third man to get a single
fullish ball outside off, Marsh pushes it towards extra cover

Marsh is gone, he chips a length delivery to the two-metre tall Peter Fulton at short cover, Fulton had to jump to hold on to that chance, good reflexes from Fulton, Marsh had looked in good touch during his short stay
Ponting defends his first ball towards cover
fullish ball on middle and leg, Ponting defends it to the leg side this time
a bit of width outside off, Ponting drops the ball to the offside and thinks of a single, finally decides against it
Warner clobbers a length ball into the ground and then to Vettori at short cover, Vettori didn't know too much about that one, but manages to stop the ball
slower, back of a length ball, Warner tries to work it to square leg, but is rapped on the pads, appeal for lbw but that pitched outside leg
angling away from the left hander, Warner defends it on the off
short ball, Warner goes for his favourite pull, mistimes it towards midwicket
overpitched on offstump, Ponting gets on the front foot and taps the ball towards mid-off
the length's shorter this time, Ponting pushes the ball towards cover, no run there and Ponting's yet to get off the mark
length ball on off, Warner tries to power it past mid-off, timing wasn't too good on that shot
short ball, again a tight line on off, Ponting shuffles across and tries to play it past mid-off, doesn't beat the fielder
he's off the mark this time,  bouncer this time, outside off, Ponting pulls it towards fine leg
punched powerfully to mid-off, Ponting was off for the single from the non-striker's end, Warner wisely sends him back

Warner's gone, similar dismissal to Marsh's, shortish ball, gave Warner room to free his arms, he cuts it but gives Fulton at short cover a much simple catch, Fulton didn't have to move and that came to him at a nice catchable height, around his chest
Clarke defends his first ball after confidently getting on to the front foot
back of a length, on off, Ponting opens the face as he plays it towards backward point
same length, on middle and off this time, Ponting blocks it off the backfoot towards cover
strays onto the legside this time, Ponting flicks it to deep square leg, Iain O Brien has to do the fielding from fine leg, the batsmen get back for the third
test Clarke with the bouncer, the batsman evades that one quite easily by ducking
length ball on off, Clarke walks down the track and defends the ball towards the offside
holds back the length a bit, no run for Clarke again, this time he punches the ball to the fielder at mid-off
Ponting takes a couple of steps down the track as he jabs the ball toward cover
short ball, Ponting guides the ball towards backward point

Ponting's run out! he turns a full ball towards square leg , Neil Broom is the fielder, he's on to the ball in a flash, the throw is fantastic as well, powerful and accurate, McCullum whips the bails off and Ponting is a couple of feet short of the crease
David Hussey gets off the mark by turning his first ball to fine leg
digs in the bouncer, Clarke is well out of its way, that was so high it was called a wide
slower delivery outside off, Clarke tries to dab it towards the offside, he's beaten
angling into the batsman, Clarke gets on the front foot and defends
starts off with a good delivery, on offstump, Hussey defends it back to the bowler
similar line, slightly outside off, Hussey tips it towards point and the batsmen pinch a single
opens the face of the bat and guides it towards gully
a touch shorter this time, Clarke plays it with soft hands towards point
keeps the ball in the corridor outside off, Hussey shoulders arms to this one
much wider outside off this time, Hussey watches it sail through to the keeper
starts with an on-target ball, on a length on off, Clarke defends off the front foot
pitching on middle, Clarke works it to square leg for a single
Hussey takes his cue from Clarke, repeats  the shot Clarke played and that's another single
Clarke waltzes down the track and defends it to the leg side
much quicker delivery, Clarke guides it to backward point
gets on the front foot and drives to long-on for a single
defended towards mid-off by Clarke
back of a length, on offstump, Clarke mistimes his on-drive to the fielder at mid-on
on middle and leg, flicked towards short midwicket by Clarke
shortish ball, a lot of space for Clarke to work with outside off, he flashes at it but doesn't connect
much closer to the stumps, Clarke wanted to drive it through extra cover, gets a thick outside edge, runs away to third man
finishes the over with a length ball on off, Clarke gets on the front foot and defends it back to the bowler
slightly overpitched, straying on the pads, Hussey tucks it to short midwicket
outside off this time, gets a thick edge onto his pads
driven towards the fielder at point
defended back to the bowler
backs away to give himself room and cuts it behind point for a single
Clarke walks across his stumps and drops the ball to the leg side
on middle and leg, Hussey can't capitalise on that one as his flick goes straight towards the fielder at midwicket
slightly outside off, Hussey drives it through the covers for a boundary, Australia need more of those
pitched up by O'Brien, driven forcefully to the fielder at cover
wide outside off, Hussey shoulders arms to that one
back of a length, on middle stump, Hussey defends it back towards the bowler
a hint of movement away after pitching well outside off, Hussey goes for the drive, a big outside edge sends the ball flying towards third man
shuffles across and plays an offstump ball to mid-on
wristily worked away towards square leg for a single
nicely tossed up, pitching just outside off, Clarke defends watchfully off the front foot
Clarke comes charging out of his crease, Vettori fires it in short, Clarke is forced to defend
just outside off, Clarke backs away to make room and cuts it towards backward point
another flighted delivery, Hussey was looking to work it to the legside, but can only defend it back to the bowler
starts with a well-directed bouncer, outside off stump, Clarke shapes for the pull but doesn't go for the stroke
Shot!, length is not as short this time, and it's on offstump, Clarke pulls that authoritatively off the front foot
fuller ball, on middle and leg, turned to fine leg
easy single for Hussey as he helps a wide ball to third man

Another run-out! Clarke's gone, he square drives it past the diving backward point, Guptill does the fielding at the boundary, the throw is wonderful again, one-bounce and on top of the stumps, Clarke's inches short of making it as McCullum takes off the bails
Michael Hussey jabs his first ball towards point
played with soft hands by David towards gully
whipped away to midwicket for Michael Hussey's first run
flat delivery, David inside-edge it to short fine leg
runs it down to third man for a single
driven to mid-off for a single
outside off, Michael Hussey lifts his bat and lets the ball go

strikes first ball, David Hussey's caught behind down the legside, short and angling down, goes for a paddle-pull, McCullum moves over to the leg side to take the catch, David Hussey's furious with the decision
tossed up, on offstump, Haddin gets forward and defends
length ball, Haddin blocks it off the backfoot
overpitched on middle and leg, Haddin gets his first run by tucking it to the leg side
length ball outside off, Hussey gets on the backfoot and defends watchfully
another display of Hussey's backfoot defensive ends the over
tossed up on the stumps and he lunges forward in defence
tossed up, gets a long way forward and defends
tossed up and defended
flatter and drifting onto leg stump, Haddin defends it back
flat and sliding into Haddin, who lunges and stabs the ball to midwicket, sets off, Hussey is quick to call him on, McCullum shouts at Taylor to hustle with the throw but he's a fraction too late
tossed up on the stumps and he plays it watchfully
slides down leg stump and Haddin turns it to midwicket
flatter ball, shorter too, and Haddin plays it off the back foot
tosses it up just outside off and he comes forward to push it away
lovely loop on that one, dipping on Hussey, who pushes it to leg
flat on off stump and he pushes it off the back foot
flat on middle and off and punched back to Patel
flights it wide and Hussey eases into a good-looking drive square through the off side, its into the gap and he runs hard, Elliott gives chase and pulls off a great dive
short and spinning away and Haddin dabs it to backward point
tosses it up to bring Haddin onto the front foot, patting it back to Vettori
lands it on the dime again, offering no quarter, and so Haddin blocks
very nagging line this, plenty of flight, landing on the seam, and defended
ends the over with another delivery on off stump which is defended
short and wide and cut out to the deep cover sweeper for one
oh shot, Haddin! Lovely use of the feet, just a shimmy down the track and then an effortless chip straight back down the ground and its into the crowd, where a fan drops it
fired in flat this time and he turns it to the on side fielder
again flat on the stumps, turned away, sets off and the throw is late
gently lobs it up outside off stump, it drifts in and Hussey drives to cover
spins back in off a short length and he runs it right to backward point
tossed up on a length, committing Hussey firmly onto the front foot
drifts in and he clips it across the stumps into the gap at midwicket
eases forward, opens the face, and steers the ball to backward point
spins in, Haddin onto the front foot, then goes back and runs it fine
tossed up, veers a bit straight and Haddin deflects it wide of square leg
fuller and flatter on middle and off and he stretches well forward
tosses it up wide, it drifts in and Hussey cuts it square on the off side
starts advancing, Patel sees him and fires it in, and Haddin defends
spins in off a length, Haddin makes room and then guides it away
gives it some air outside off and Hussey square-drives it to point
tosses it up down the stumps, Haddin works it off the pads to square leg
fuller delivery outside off, he comes well forward and pushes to cover
tosses up on off stump, Hussey uses his feet and on-drives a single
shorter length, not much turn and Haddin pushes it off the back foot
slower ball, well flighted on the seam and Haddin can only defend
a tad too wide, Haddin opens the face but can't beat backward point
flatter on middle and leg and Haddin works it to midwicket
comes well onto the front foot and dabs the ball in front of point, hustling
stars to drift into leg stump and Hussey works it into the gap
comes a long way forward and takes on the full, driving to mid-on
flights it up gently outside off, Hussey gets forward with a square drive
starts walking down, Patel keeps it short, Haddin taps it to midwicket
uses his feet and whips the ball to midwicket again
holds back the length a tad and Hussey pushes the ball to cover
starts off a touch short on the stumps and Hussey short-arm jabs it between midwicket and square leg, into the gap, the fielder runs after it and cuts it off in the deep
short again, Haddin goes for his shot but cannot connect
130.5ks, short on the stumps and he gets tall to defend
makes some room and chips the fuller ball in the air over cover, its not timed all the well but he cleared the in field and picked up a couple more
short of a length just outside off and he dabs it off the open face to gully
short of a length, pitches on leg and slants across, its poked to point
short ball, Haddin backs away and cuts from on top of off stump
this time he beats the fielder, again rocking back to give the ball a hard cut, it bisects a tumbling Broom at backward point and Haddin gets a pleasing boundary
tossed up on the stumps and he watchfully turns it to midwicket
tossed up outside off, Hussey drives inside-out to the off side
comes a few paces down and clips the ball past midwicket to Elliott
flighted on off stump, he comes across and clips right to midwicket
dragged in short down the stumps and he pulls with control into the opening at square leg and collects a single with the sweeper walking in to do the fielding
pitches much fuller and Hussey gets right over it, just tapping it to the off side and calling Haddin across, Taylor swoops in, collects, and has a shy but it doesn't work out
pitches on a length and stays low, looks like the slower off cutter, Haddin does well to pick it and gets the bat down in time, though he knew it could have been otherwise
makes room for himself and forces the shorter ball between cover and point, its not timed to perfection but Haddin's innovativeness gets him a couple more
backs away to leg again and slaps the ball to backward point
slower ball, just 117ks, pitches just outside leg stump and swings in, Hussey shuffles across and easily glances that off his pads in front of short fine leg
pitches it full on off stump and Hussey pushes the ball to point
pitches on about leg stump and this time he turns it to square leg
short of a length and he gets right in line, defending off the back foot
overpitched outside off stump, Hussey miscues a drive to short cover
pitches wider, Hussey gets forward but cannot beat the man at point
pitched up again and a firm drive down the ground can't beat mid-off
pitches back of a length and Haddin steers it to backward point
good shot, Haddin pushes a full ball on off stump with a full face and bunts it straight back past the stumps, calling for the sharp single that raises the 50-run stand
full on off stump, Hussey stabs at it and mistimes it back to Mills
overpitched a tad wider and he cracks a drive straight to short cover
a tad wider still and he dabs it wide of backward point for one
130.7ks, short on off stump, Haddin hops and defends to leg
full on the stumps, 119ks and swinging, Hussey pushes it back to O'Brien, who collects and feigns a throw back to the batsman
short and wide but he cannot cut it past a tumbling Taylor at short cover
oh well bowled, that one is pitched up with some swing, Hussey pokes at it and gets an inside edge very narrowly sneaking back past leg stump
full on the stumps and whipped past midwicket for a single
pitches it up on middle and off and Hussey chips it back in the air back past O'Brien and it beats mid-on as well
pitched up again and he pushes it down the ground for one
sees the width and cracks it square but straight to the man at point
change of pace, 111.7ks, on leg stump and he can't clip it well
superb timing on this occasion, picking another slower delivery and comes well forward, making room and punching on the rise into the gap in the covers
pitches on middle and he defends to the on side
short of a length, he steers it off the back foot to backward point
dragged on! Haddin advances to a full one just outside off stump and goes for a drive but can only succeed in inside-edging back onto his stumps and Mills celebrates
on a length, coming back into the batsman, Hussey works it off the backfoot towards cover
nicely tossed up, on a length, the batsman defends it off the front foot
drives confidently towards cover, but straight to the fielder
overpitched on legstump, tickled down the legs side by Hopes
flicked towards short midwicket, no run
carefully defends a tossed up delivery off the front foot
Vettori tosses one wide outside off, Hussey reaches out and gets that away behind point, Broom does the fieldeing
overpitched, Hussey lunges forward and opens the face to guide the ball towards gully
came forward and pushed it to cover
overpitched on offstump, Hussey deadbats it back to the bowler
on middle and leg, Hussey backs away and thumps it towards cover
length ball, pitching just outside off, Hussey waits for it on the backfoot and taps it to the off side
flighted delivery, just outside off, Hopes was looking to drive, gets a thick outside edge past the keeper
this turn it turns past leg, Hopes tucks it behind square, he was thinking of taking the second but he dropped his bat as he turned
Hussey shows the full face of the bat and defends it solidly
on the pads, Hussey works it towards midwicket for a single
again Hopes is undone by the spin, he was aiming for the drive, gets a leading edge towards mid-on
tossed up, blocked back towards the bowler
nice length there, Hussey is drawn onto the front foot as he jabs it towards mid-on
whistling down leg this time, Hussey whips it towards fine leg
gives that ball some air, Hopes backs away to make room for the cut, which goes straight to point
solid front-foot defence from Hopes
Vettori sticks to a nagging line outside off, Hopes defends off the front foot
on middle and leg, nudged towards short midwicket
another flighted delivery, Hussey rocks back and slogs that to his favourite midwicket area for a six
sliding down the legside, well taken by the keeper
on the pads again, easily worked to square leg for a single
swept by Hopes, by it is mistimed, goes straight to the fielder
looks to play him straight this time, easy single to long-on
width provided, Hussey cuts it square for a single
on a length, outside off, Hopes chops that to backward point for another single
cramps Hopes with an offstump line, Hopes was looking to cut, it rolls away towards the bowler, batsmen pinch a quick single
full ball on middle, Hussey opens the face to guide it to backward point, placement isn't perfect, no run
steps out to drive it down to long-off, batsmen saunter through for a single
back of a length, good, tight line, Hopes jabs it towards extra cover

slower ball, short and wide, Hopes chops it to point, straight to Guptill, Hussey was backing up a long way, a direct hit at the non-striker's end would have caught him way short, the throw misses though
flicked to short mid wicket for a quick single
straying on to the pads, turned past mid-on , deep midwicket has to come across to cut if off
on middle and leg, this time hopes punches it to Grant Elliott at mid-on, who fires in a throw at the stumps and catches Hopes just as he is finishing the run
defended back to the bowler by Hussey
overpitched, Hussey finds the gap through the covers, Peter Fulton gives chase and keeps the batsmen to two
full ball on off, easy single down to long-off
yorker on middle stump, Hopes pushes it to Elliott and sets off for a single, could have been tight if there was a direct hit
short of a length on off, blocked back to the bowler by Hopes
angling into offstump, Hopes whips it away to midwicket
slower ball, 112kph, on middle stump, Hussey eases it down to long-off
follows that up with a good bouncer, Hopes is surprised by that, but dodges it
on legstump, Hopes turns it to square leg, nice placement from Hopes gives batsmen time to take two
back of a length, in the corridor outside off, Hopes wafts at it but is beaten

first ball of the Powerplay gets a wicket, Hussey has to go, he tried to chip a length ball over the infield, mid-off was on the edge of the circle, and it's a simple catch for him, Hussey's innings ends at 49
shortish ball on legstump, Johnson prods it towards midwicket
length ball on off, driven powerfully by Hopes, hits O'Brien on his knees and there's no run available
Hopes is gone, both the settled batsmen are dismissed in the same over, he was trying to slam that over the covers, gets a top edge which balloons in the air for a dolly to Vettori to mid-off
slower ball first up for Bracken, shortish ball, hits him on the pads in front of middle, New Zealand are convinced he's lbw but that was going a bit high
short ball, drops his wrists and lets it go
punched to cover point by Johnson for a single
angling in towards the offstump, Bracken shoulders arms to that one
Bracken's lbw this time, he was attempting to work that towards midwicket, hit him in front of middle, looked out, though Hawkeye suggests it might have just gone down leg
shortish ball on offstump, Tait pushes it towards cover
length ball on middle, Tait was backing away as he defended it towards the bowler
full straight ball on middle stump, Tait gets behind the line and defends
overpitched and angling away from the batsman, Johnson taps it towards mid-off
much shorter this time, at the batsman's body, Johnson tries to chop it behind point, can't beat the fielder
Shot! flatbats a slower ball straight down the ground after clearing the front , O'Brien had no chnace of getting a hand on that
looks to drive this time, but he's beaten by the ball that's angling away from him
powerfully slammed down the ground, New Zealand have pushed mid-on to the boundary so that's only a single
full, slower ball, 119kmh, Tait does well to keep that one out, he digs it out towards cover
short ball outside off, Johnson backed away to give himself more room and powers that to the offside but the fielder at point makes a diving stop
length ball, on middle and off, Tait goes back and blocks it back to the bowler
slightly overpitched, just outside off, Tait goes after that one, takes the aerial route, over mid-off, timing isn't too good, but there's enough in the shot to take the ball to the boundary
shorter ball this time, on off, Tait was backing away, he beaten as he tries to nudge it towards third man
Tait takes a couple of paces behind legstump again, Mills follows him, Tait manages to taps that to the offside for a single
full ball on the pads, Johnson flicks it for a single towards midwicket to retain the strike
yorker outside off, Johnson can only squeeze it to backward point
length ball on middle stump, Johnson smashes that down the ground, beats a diving long-on for a boundary
tipped towards mid-off, Johnson declines the single
low full toss, Johnson swipes it down the ground again, this time long-off gets across in time to keep the batsmen down to a single
Tait goes for an extremely ambitious shot, shortish ball on middle stump, Tait backs away and tries to chip it over the wicketkeeper, beaten
this time the ball does fly over the keeper, O'Brien digs in the bouncer, Tait goes for the hook, gets a top edge and that's a boundary
Johnson throws his bat at a wide ball, bottom hand comes off after that shot, goes towards deep point but Johnson again doesn't want the single
Cracking shot! low full toss on the offstump, a lovely swing of the bat from Johnson sends the ball rocketing back in the direction it came
Johnson shows us he's not all about power, the bowler follows him as Johnson backs away, the batsman just opens the face of the bat to guide it through the first slip region
and that's the end of the innings, Johnson goes for a big swipe over midwicket, doesn't make contact with the ball, which homes in on the leg bail, Australia fold for 181

inn2.comm: cracker of a delivery to start with, length ball on off, squares McCullum up, he tries to play it to leg, gets a leading edge which drops just short of backward point
McCullum's gone lbw this time, stunning start from Tait, that was 145.7 kmh, McCullum went on the backfoot to defend, hits his pads in front, umpire didn't spot a huge inside edge
jags away from the batsman after pitching on a length outside off, Fulton leaves it well alone
cranking up the pace here, that was 149.8, full and swung away, Fulton is beaten all ends up, it slides under his bat through to the keeper
shorter ball this time, tight line around off, Fulton defends off the backfoot
late swing for Tait but that was too wide outside off for the umpire's liking
finishes the over with another testing delivery, back of a length, pitching just outside off, it had Fulton feeling for it before he withdrew his bat to let it sail through to the keeper
Bracken starts with a delivery on the pads, Guptill tucks it towards the leg side
shortish ball from Bracken, Guptill gets across and defends it, an inside edge  onto his pads
length ball on off, Guptill drives uppishly towards mid-off, lands short of David Hussey who makes a full-length dive to his right to stop the ball
similar line and length, this time Guptill defends solidly back to the bowler, showing the full face of the bat
just outside off, Guptill bravely lets that one go through to the keeper
slightly wider than the previous one, Guptill shoulders arms again
starts off with a full ball down the leg side, he'll have to bowl that one again
goes to the other extreme of the previous ball, 151.5 kmh bouncer way outside off now
outswinger, Fulton looks to cut it but is beaten
overpitched on middle and off, Fulton gets behind the line and defends
length ball, nice, tight line on offstump, Fulton defends it back to the bowler
fishes at a full swinging ball outside off, he's beaten this time, but that's a dangerous ploy
back of a length on off, moves a touch away from the right-hand batsman, Fulton defends confidently toward cover
wide ball outside off, Fulton leaves that one to the keeper, nearly called a wide but Tait gets away with that one
overpitched on legstump, easy pickings for Guptill, he flicks that to the midwicket boundary to get the first runs off the bat for New Zealand
outside the off stump, Guptill gets on the front foot, and shoulders arms
drives a length ball towards extra cover, wasn't too far from Ponting at short cover, who gets a hand to it
angling across Guptill, who defends it to the legside
in the channel just outside off, Guptill isn't interested in that one, leaves that for the keeper
overpitched on off, driven forcefully towards mid-off, but too forcefully to give the batsmen time to take a single
short ball, well outside off, Fulton isn't tempted into chasing that one, it sails through to the keeper, that one was 148kmh
angling into the batsman, length ball, birthday boy Fulton defends it towards mid-on
Fulton's beaten again, pitched up by Tait, around the offstump, Fulton goes for the booming drive, the away swing gets the better of him
low full toss on offstump, Fulton punches it back to the bowler
short of a length, and angling into Fulton, thuds into his pads as he tries to defend off the backfoot

Fulton gets off the mark with a superbly-timed off dirve, it was again a back of a length delivery, Fulton just pushed it in the gap, Marsh was giving chase, he never looked  like catching up and he falls over ten yards away from the boundary
starts off with a well-directed bouncer, goes straight at Guptill's chest, who manages to awkwardly defend it
sensational shot! length ball on legstump, Guptill flicks it off his pads for an effortless six

hits Guptill on the pad, he's not a long way forward, there's a big appeal from the Australians but that looked like it was pitching outside leg, Hawkeye suggests it was pitching on middle and leg though
this time he defends it towards mid-off off the backfoot
short ball on legstump, Guptill gets behind the line and defends it solidly back to the bowler
more backfoot defence from Guptill, this time he drops the ball at his feet
drives it to Ponting at short cover
wide, way too wide outside off
back on target this time, length ball pitching on middle, slightly slower ball, Fulton lunges forward and defends
slightly outside off, Fulton steps across and drives through the line, can't beat the fielder at extra cover though
slower ball again, 122.7k, pitching just outside leg, Fulton defends it off the backfoot
Fulton fortunate to survive, he was aiming to work that delivery from middle stump to the legside, takes a leading edge and flies over the covers
ooh, Fulton didn't have much clue about that one either, he was trying to defend it back to the bowler, gets an inside edge, and the ball could so easily have rolled back onto his stumps
length ball on legstump to start, Guptill gets on his toes and blocks it towards square leg
on middle and off this time, defended solidly by Guptill
good length ball from Johnson, about a foot outside off, Guptill lifts his bat and lets it go
Johnson reverts to attacking the legstump, Guptill was looking to work that behind square, gets an edge and the ball drops at his feet
Johnson keeps Guptill pinned to the backfoot, this time the batsman defends towards the offside
pushes the length up a touch this time, on offstump, Guptill defends again, this time towards extra cover
Bracken's on target again, length ball, defended off the backfoot to short cover
this time Fulton chases a short ball outside off, goes for a powerful cut, doesn't make contact though
strays on to the pads, Fulton hepls himself to an easy single by flicking that to square leg
length delivery, defended off the front foot by Guptill towards cover
the length is a lot shorter this time, pushing Guptill back, and he blocks it to the offside
a bit of width for Guptill to work with, he's thrashes that behind square but can't beat a diving Michael Clarke
On Fulton's legstump, called a legbye after Haddin fails to collect the ball, but that was actually a wide down the leg side
slower ball, on a length, angling across the batsman who's beaten as he goes for the big drive
another delivery that's angling across the batsman, a bit wider than the previous one, Guptill shoulders arms
Johnson goes back to the leg-stump line, flicked by Guptill to midwicket for two
driven crisply by Fulton to mid-off, no run
pitches on a length and he defends it off the front foot to point

bowled em! Bracken strikes with a full delivery that pitches on off stump and hurries Guptill into a loose defensive push, but he's very late on the shot and the ball nips back in and draws the faintest of inside edges back onto the stumps

oh big shout first ball! Bracken again serves it up full, marginally pitching outside leg stump, the ball swings back in and raps an itchy Taylor as he falls forward, replays suggest the ball was doing a bit too much, but it was more about where it initially pitched
full again and he thrusts forward to defend
pitches on about off stump and Taylor stabs it to the off side
pitches on leg stump and slides on, Taylor shuffles and defends
short of a length outside off stump, Fulton pushes off the back foot
so close! Johnson pitches it up on the stumps, Fulton plays an attempted flick and its back in the air toward a diving bowler, bouncing tantalizingly short
too much movement and the ball swing wide of the stumps
serves it up outside off stump and Fulton drives on the up to cover
nagging length, not full enough to drive and so Fulton defends
much fuller this time, 142.5ks, Fulton has a go and misses
back of a length and seaming across Taylor, who shoulders arms
pitched up and he pushes it straight to cover
pitches outside off stump and wobbles away and no shot offered
no room to work with at all and Taylor defends to the off side
again its pitched up around off stump and he pushes it to cover
pitched up and seaming with the angle, Taylor shoulders arms
pitches back of a length and slides back in, stays low and Fulton just gets a bit of bat on it, a stifled appeal from Johnson, indicative of two sounds on that occasion

well held, Mitchell! A very scratchy innings comes to an end courtesy a superb reflex catch from Johnson, who pitches it up on off stump and then sticks out his left hand as he tumbles down in his followthrough, plucking the checked off-drive back in the air rather excellently
pitches short of a length down leg stump and Elliott hops across to flick it into the gap, opening his account immediately
pitches on the stumps and stays low and he turns it to midwicket
beaten! Johnson pitches it up just outside off stump and gets the ball to shape away and then straighten, Elliott walks into the push and misses very narrowly
full down leg stump, Elliott walks across the sticks and misses, and the ball narrowly misses taking out leg stick
and he's welcomed with a smashing drive through the covers from Taylor, getting to the pitch of that wide one and hitting it cleanly into the gap
better length, holding it back to get Taylor defending to cover
pitches on off stump, Taylor walks into a defensive push to extra cover
pitched up wide and he shoulders arms off the front foot
full just outside off stump and he defends it to the off side
pitches on a length and some very conservative defensive stuff follows
slides down leg stump and he turns it into the gap at square leg
bounces well down the leg stump and a wide is called
thats really overpitched, sliding out the hand, well past off stump

tip-and-run from Elliott, defending to cover and sprinting off in search of the 22-yard Olympic Gold, his partner Taylor is struggling as Clarke swoops in and misses a one-handed throw toward the stumps, that was pretty close there
short of a length and sitting up, Taylor gets tall and shoulders arms
swings back down leg stump, Taylor is late on the attempted nudge
overpitched wide of the stumps and Taylor laces a square-drive into the gap behind point, third man runs across but cannot cut it off, that was scorching shot
pitches down leg stump and he tucks it down to deep square
125ks, pitches wide of the stumps and no shot offered
again Hopes pitches a tad wide and Taylor shoulders arms
drifting down the pads and Taylor plays a perfect leg glance for four
pitches on a length, Taylor comes forward and nudges to point

dropped by Johnson at third man! Taylor sees width and flashes the bat at it, getting a top edge that spirals down to the fielder running in, who slides onto his knees and clutches at it, but fails to pick it cleanly in the end, was tough but needed to be taken
pitched up and eases it to point off the front foot
pitches just outside off stump and Elliott defends to point
banged in short down leg stump, 142ks, Elliott walks across and aims to deflect it off the hips but cannot connect, the ball clips his gloves and dribbles to Haddin
overpitched down the stumps, 144ks, flicked to square leg
short on the body and Elliott hops across to deflect it to fine leg, that single raises the 50 for New Zealand, a long time coming, I might add
pitched up outside off stump and he drives on the rise, square on the off side, just picking the gap and Taylor and Elliott sprint back and forth three times
overpitched on the stumps, he shuffles and clips off the toes to square leg
comes forward and watchfully defends a length delivery
pitches on a good length, Elliott drives on the rise to Ponting at short cover
another tidy delivery on a length and more watchful defending
drives a fuller one to Ponting at short cover, who fumbles the ball
pitches on a length and straightens, Taylor defends it back to Hopes
short ball outside off, 130ks, and Taylor ducks low
slides down the pads, Elliott gets a faint tickle that beats Haddin
short outside off stump this time and he hops in line to defend
short on off stump now and he gets behind the ball to defend
bangs it in shorter, he goes for a pull across the line and misses, the ball clips his midriff and parries down towards short third man
better length, with some swing, and its defended off the front foot
pitches full and he defends off the front foot to cover
short of a length on leg stump and he tucks it to midwicket
full on about off stump and he taps it back to Hopes
pitches it up, Elliott drives off the front foot to Ponting at short cover
much wider and fuller and he opens the face, steering to third man
pitched up and he pushes it to the off side
full again and he squirts it to the man at point for one
tosses it up full and Taylor flashes a drive into the covers
tossed up on a better length and he defends it back solidly
gets some room and hits the ball square but can't beat point
tossed up, this time Elliott walks two paces down and defends
flatter and shorter and he punches off the back foot to cover
flights it up and gets some drift, Elliott pushes it back to Clarke
makes room and edges it down to third man, that ball kicked like a mule
pitches it up and this time he defends it back
easy catch! Hopes pitches it on a length, Elliott drives on the rise to short cover, where Mike Hussey falls to his right and intercepts the shot, that was like catching practice
pitches short of a length and he gets up to leave it be
fuller, a tad, and he leaves it be as it wobbles to Haddin
hits a good length and Broom gets bat on it, defending to the off side
tossed up on off stump and Taylor defends it back patiently
tossed up again and he pushes it off the front foot to cover
lobs it up and he collects on the full, bunting it down to long-on
shorter and he goes back and pushes with an inside edge
short outside off stump, cut wide of the fielder, they come back for the second and  flat direct hit comes back to Haddin's ends, replays confirm Broom is home safe
tossed up and he defends it back solidly to end the over
pitches wide of off stump and he dabs the ball to the off side
hits a length and he forces the ball to Clarke at point
gets some room and cuts hard but Clarke intercepts at point
pitches on middle and off and he presents a full face back
pitches it up and Taylor plays a loose shot outside off the stump
overpitched and he miscues the drive to cover, ending a maiden over
lands it on a good length outside off and the ball holds its line before reaching Haddin
fires in the yorker outside off and Broom fails to dig it out
tries to turn it away to the on side but he gets an inside edge onto his boot
chance to drive through the covers on the front foot but he fails to beat Hussey in that position
the slower ball, he reaches out and glides it down to third man
full on the offstump and driven straight to mid-off, New Zealand aren't able to break free here
tries to work it to the onside but gets a leading edge to the off side
full on middle and leg and he pushes it away firmly to mid-on
he gets a lot of width outside off to cut but he picks Clarke at backward point, a scoring opportunity missed
slightly full angling towards the pads, he gets his bat behind the line and pushes it to mid-off
fullish in length outside off, he gets forward and pats it wide of mid-off
gets forward for the square drive and times it pretty well wide of backward point, Johnson sprints across from third man and cuts it off
flighted on middle and leg and he drives firmly but can;t beat the bowler
drifts outside off, he gets forward and steers it wide of point
angled on the pads, he clips it to square leg
full on middle and leg and softly tapped to the on side
flighted on middle and leg, he defends to the off side
lunges forward and defends back to the bowler
very slow through the air, he gets forward and drives firmly
gets down the track and nicely whips him away wide of midwicket
opens the face of the bat and steers him down to the vacant slips region
thrusts forward and defends
commits to the front foot and a firm drive is intercepted by Clarke at short mid-off
angled on the pads, he works it away down to fine leg
full outside off and driven to the off side
gets to the pitch of the ball and drives to mid-off
slower through the air, he waits on it before cutting to short third man
Run-out appeal! He nudges it to square leg and quickly sends his partner back, a direct hit by David Hussey has all the Australians celebrating, the third umpire takes a look and Taylor's safe
slides down the leg side and it appears to hit Broom's bat before running down to fine leg but the umpire calls it a wide
makes room and cuts to mid-off
gets forward and defends to the off side
flighted on middle and pushed to the off side
slower through the air, he gets on his knee and sweeps to deep square-leg
flighted outside off and he square drives to point
fires it down the leg side and the batsman misses the sweep, wide called, his back foot is back at the crease
flighted on the pads and he forcefully pushes it past the gap at deep midwicket, Hilfenhaus does the fielding
full outside off, he pushes it wide of point
lands it on a good length on the off stump, he gets behind the line and pats it to the on side
slides down the leg side and the ball clips his pads and very nearly beats Haddin who does well to dive and cut it off
gives him width outside off and he slices it down to third man
Tait fires in a fast yorker and Broom gets his bat down and digs it out, the ball bounces and beats first slip and runs away for four
full outside off, he pushes it to the off side
fires in a full length ball and he digs it to the on side
tries to work it past the bowler but Hussey does well to stop it
slides wide down the leg side
flighted outside off and he pushes it towards mid-off
tucked towards cover
shuffles and clips it to midwicket
pushes it through the line to long-on and the 100 comes up after a lot of struggle
flighted on middle and leg and pushed back to the bowler
Tait cramps him for room as the ball jags back in and slices him in half almost, the ball lobs off his pads to the keeper
gets forward to drive but the ball clips his pad first and then bat, there's a stifled appeal but he was well outside the line of off stump
Tait searches for the yorker and slides down the leg side, he clips it away fine and Bracken dives in vain at fine leg, great effort all the same
angles it on the pads again but this time he clips it wide of midwicket
goes for a wide slash on the half-forward prod but misses it completely, the ball shoots back in and nearly shaves the edge
holds the length back on the offstump and he gets behind the line and defends
lands it on a good length and he tries to steer it away to the on side but checks his stroke and pats it back to the bowler
bowls it straight again and he settles for another defensive stroke
angled on middle and leg, he clips it to the on side
slightly short of a length outside off and he cuts but mistimes the shot to backward point
fuller in length outside off and steered to point
he finds the length to pull but he mistimes the shot and places it wide of midwicket
clipped to midwicket

Australia claw back, now there's a bit of controversy here, Clarke gets it to skid through on a good length, Broom makes a lot of room to cut but he's beaten for pace, the ball appears to clip the top of the off bail but replays indicate that Haddin had his gloves in front of the stumps before the ball could make contact. Did the ball actually hit the stumps? Did Haddin whip off the bails by mistake? Very inconclusive but no wonder Broom looked perplexed as he walked back
slides down the leg side and he nudges it to fine leg
steps down to a full toss and he clubs it away down to the spaces between long-on and deep midwicket
gets forward and pushes it to long-on
full outside off and driven to mid-off
gets forward and pushes it back to the bowler
defends back to the bowler
punches it firmly to Clarke at mid-off
defended back to the bowler
the ball skids through sharply and he makes use of the extra pace to glide it wide of the keeper and short third man
stays back to a good length ball and defends
gets forward and steers a full ball to cover point
gets forward and steers it wide of cover
pushed to the deep on the on side
slides on the pads and he clips it to the on side
tapped back to the bowler
stays back to a good length ball and clips it wide of square leg
almost edged! He lands it outside off and gets it to slant away and Mills pokes at it
bangs it in short, he attempts to hook it away but misses it
pushes it to cover point and they contemplate a single, the fielder has a shy at the stumps at the bowler's end
fires it full and quick outside off and he fails to dig out the yorker
full outside off and driven wide of backward point
full outside off and he drives, the sweeper cover fielder runs across to cut it off
this one skids through, he gets a thick inside edge and the ball bobs off the pitch and rolls to the keeper
wide outside off and he has a wild swing at the ball, pretty close to being called a wide
hangs his bat outside off and steers it to third man
lands it outside off and Mills gets off the strike with a glide to third man
gets across the line and works it to long-on
the slower ball this time, he drives hard and the underedge falls short of the keeper
drives forcefully to the off side and he fails to beat the field, it's now down to a run a ball
goes for a forceful square drive but he gets a thick inside edge on to his body
short of a length outside off and he withdraws the stroke
swing and a miss, he makes room to crash it through the off side but he's beaten for pace
full just outside the line of the offstump, he gets forward and steers it firmly to third man
the slower ball, on the stumps. he gets behind the line and steers it wide of cover
it's a low full toss outside off and he really reaches out to slam it away but the ball makes contact with the toe of the bat and he places it back to the bowler instead
goes for a huge heave to the on side but he gets a thick outside edge, Hopes runs across and the ball nearly spins away from him and runs to the boundary, luckily he gets a hand to it
jams it the yorker outside off and Haddin appeals half-heartedly for the outside edge
and Mills gets off to a good start, he gets width outside off from round the wicket, he stays at the wicket and glides it wide of the vacant slips region and short third man
that's a cracker of a shot, Bracken overpitches outside off from round the wicket, he drives elegantly past the covers and the ball scorches through the turf
angles it on the pads and he whips it away wide of square leg
attempts a yorker but it's a low full toss which he works away down to long-off
full in length outside off, he gets behind the line and forces it to long-off
it's a low full toss on middle and leg and he pushes it away towards long-on
jams it on a good length on the offstump, he gets behind the line and pushes it back to the bowler

Into the crowd! Can we have the ball back please? Taylor gets to his fifty in style, he backs away from the stumps, gets underneath a pitched up delivery on middle and leg and heaves it over deep midwicket and in to the grass embankment
slides on the pads, he shuffles and works it behind square on the on side
almost a run-out! He taps it to cover and Taylor darts out of his crease and immediately turns around and heads back and the fielder decides not to throw
full outside off, goes for the drive and misses
take that! Tait overpitches outside of and Mills gets forward and caresses it wide of cover, perfectly timed, that's 11 off the over
fires in the yorker, the ball bounces high off the pitch after the batsman drives back and Bracken gets his fingers to intercept it
makes room and Bracken cleverly holds the length and forces the batsman to check his shot, he fends it to the off side
Mills backs away and Bracken once again follows him and directs it at his body, he settles for a single with a nudge to the on side
the slower ball, it's short in length and he swats it in to the gap at deep midwicket
slices it firmly to the off side and Clarke is simply brilliant at point as he slides to his left and intercepts it one handed
comes round the wicket, he gets behind the line and pushes it to the off side
comes over the wicket, he fires that full outside off and he drives firmly to long-off
you can't bowl high full tosses at this stage, it's a freebie for Taylor outside off as he reaches out and slashes it off the middle of the bat and beats backward point
good comeback by Johnson as he fires the yorker outside off and Taylor fails to get underneath it
inconsistent stuff from Johnson as he slides it wide down the leg side, the batsman calmly lets it go
drifts on the pads and Taylor has the opportunity to whip it away but he fails to beat Ponting at midwicket
clips it wide of square leg and Warner is simply fantastic as he sprints across, slides and saves a four, he limits it to two runs, the throw is too high though for Haddin
full toss on middle and leg and he firmly pushes it through the line to long-on, there's protection there
bowls it short of a length and the ball clips his pads and rolls to short square leg off the hips
he exposes his stumps and tries to heave the ball to the on side but he fails to read the slower ball and the ball hits him flush on the abdomen, he's in pain

he gets a little too cheeky and loses his wicket, he makes way too much room and exposes all three stumps, Tait fires in a fast yorker and hits the middle stump, now will this wicket change things a bit?
comes round the wicket and cramps him for roo, he hops at the crease and fends off a short ball to point

Vettori steers it wide of Clarke at backward point and sets off for a sharp single, the throw is just wide and all of a sudden, a male spectator in shorts runs onto the field carrying a beach ball! An army of security personnel chase him and try to trip him, hilarious stuff at the WACA
he takes his eyes off a bouncer and the ball clips his body and rolls to the off side
it;s a full toss outside off and he fails to put it away, the outside edge is well taken by Haddin
excellent bowling by Bracken, he bowls the slower one on a yorker length and Taylor can only push it back to the bowler

a fabulous catch by Clarke and we have a twist in the tale here, Bracken pitches it up outside off, he walks across his stumps, reaches forward and slices it on the up to backward point, Clarke flings himself to his left and cups it with both hands

this is getting more dramatic! Southee taps a yorker length ball towards short mid-off and sends his partner back, the fielder under arms the ball at the stumps and misses, the fielder backing up misfields and the batsmen contemplate an over throw, Vettori is sent back again and Bracken hits the stumps, replays indicated that it was very close
beaten outside the off stump, they steal a bye
bangs it in short, he tries to hook but misses
he makes room and exposes all three stumps, he gets an inside edge past the stumps and Haddin does really well to save it, they steal a run
comes round the wicket, Vettori backs away too far and he fails to make any contact
he bangs in the bouncer from round the wicket and Vettoru ducks under it hoping it will be called a no ball, Bucknor at square leg signals one for the over
fires in the yorker outside off and he gets forward and digs it out wide of point
backs away and Tait bangs it in short, he adjusts his stroke and slices it down to third man
fires that on the blockhole and he pushes it firmly through the line to long-on
timber! Bracken bowls that deadly off cutter and Southee fails to pick the slower ball, he exposes his leg stump and tries to heave it away over square leg as the ball thuds on to his middle stump
gets forward and steers it down to backward point and the batsmen are struggling, the fielder has a shy at the bowler';s stumps and Patel is nowhere in the scene
fires in the yorker and he gets underneath a low full toss and works it away to deep square leg
just opens the face of the bat and steers it to short third man, New Zealand can't lose now, the scores are level

he's done it! Vettori's hit the winning run! Bracken bowls a full ball outside off stump, he was looking for the yorker no doubt.Vettori loves width outside off, he loves the cut, and he places the ball through backward point and yells in triumph
